article.headline: Stony Brook 75, Maine 59
article.story: STONY BROOK, N.Y. (AP) -- Mitchell Beauford scored 21 points and Ricky Lucas finished with 18 to lead Stony Brook to a 75-59 win over Maine on Sunday. Jermol Paul scored 12 and Demetrius Young had eight points and 10 rebounds for the Seawolves (4-10, 1-1 America East), who led 45-29 at halftime. Mark Socoby went 7-for-10 from 3-point range and finished with 27 points for the Black Bears (4-10, 0-1). Maine outrebounded Stony Brook 41-31 but committed 24 turnovers. The Black Bears also shot 38 percent from the field.
